      "properties": {
        "text": ""
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "\u2139\ufe0f Landmark Facial Aligner (S-06)\n\nDefaults: target_size=1024, padding=0.2.\n\n- landmarks: 5-point JSON [L-eye, R-eye, nose, L-mouth, R-mouth]. Pixel-abs or normalized (values \u2264 1.5 auto-treated as normalized). Default coords target sample_portrait.jpg.\n- target_size: 512 / 768 / 1024 (step=256). 1024 is SDXL-friendly.\n- padding: 0 = tight crop, 0.5 = half-frame reserved around face.\n\nCanonical frame (FFHQ-like, normalized): eyes @ Y=0.40, nose @ Y=0.55, mouth @ Y=0.70. Face is centered horizontally.\n\nWhy align: get a consistent crop before ControlNet / inpaint / face-detail passes. Use inverse_matrix_json output to unwrap the edited face back onto the original canvas (pair with a custom warp node or unwarp script).\n\nWarning: wrong landmarks = wrong alignment — prefer an upstream face-detector node (InsightFace / MediaPipe) instead of hand-pasting in production. Roundtrip (align + unwrap) goes through 2 bilinear resamples, so the result softens ~34/255 in uint8 — good enough for a retouch chain, not near-lossless."
      ],
      "color": "#243",
      "bgcolor": "#365"
    }
